data.title: Excellent Food and Service from Pam
data.text: The food was off the charts along with the coffee. Must try the Lechera crepes, for 3 meals  and coffee and tax only $36 wow.

data.title: Delicious
data.text: It's soooo good and so affordable. Pancakes are delicious and all :) like a mom and pop joint. It's super delicious cloud too

data.title: Simple and wonderful breakfast!
data.text: I went to Cafe Fourteen with my husband and parents on a busy Sunday morning. We had anticipated a long wait but it was only about 10 minutes.  The owner runs the front register and is extremely friendly to everyone whether you're a regular customer or brand new.  He really made us feel welcome and that was a positive start.  Our waitress was fabulous as well and had an excellent memory--usually my mom has to remind waitstaff that she takes her coffee decaf but the waitress remembered.  Though she was busy, she was very attentive and upbeat.  The food was reasonably priced and very good.  I had the cinnamon French toast which I could have easily eaten a whole ton of, my mom had pancakes which were delightfully fluffy, my husband had a skillet, and my dad had the daily special "Canadian omelete" that he really enjoyed.  I would definitely return the next time I'm in the area!!!

data.title: Good Family Pancake House
data.text: Very friendly. Greeted by owner. He & staff greeted their regular patrons by name. Food was very good. Large selection on menu. Breakfast and lunch, even dinner type items.  Clean.

data.title: Great breakfast every day
data.text: Very good breakfast and lunch; omelets and skillets are great.  Great coffee.  Very friendly, good service.  Best breakfast in the neighborhood.

data.title: Comfortable
data.text: Only available for breakfast and lunch but well worth the trip.  Good is good, staff is pleasant.  when I said I had a taste for lots of coffee, my cup was never empty.  Lots of choices for either meal and the last omelet I had was  very, very good.  Plenty to eat.

data.title: great for breakfast
data.text: Great breakfast place- service and food are quick to arrive, even when it is packed.  Oh and it does get very busy on Sunday mornings.  Kind of your classic Greek owned diner place. Love the ham off the bone here.

data.title: Best Crepes in Town
data.text: Whenever we feel like eating breakfast outside, this cafe is one of our favorite places.  All their common breakfast dishes are great and prices very reasonable.  I especially like their crepes as I found them better than specialty shops around my area.  Service is very friendly.  My only complaint is that their coffee is weak.

data.title: Many visits - Never disappointed!
data.text:
We've retired out-of-state but whenever we're in Palatine visiting the children in the area this is our official breakfast stop..
  Great food cooked the way you ask and friendly staff always on top of drink and coffee refills. The bus boys keep up with clearing tables (something we miss back home). Poached eggs, waffles, skillets, bacon and pancakes always a hit with the family.
  We'll be back for more!

data.title: Impressed
data.text: A great place for a lazy brunch. Food comes in the appropriate amount of time and there is plenty of it. Impressed that I asked for a strawberry shake that I didn't see on the menu yet the waitress made me one anyways. Got a spinach and feta omelet. They're huge stuffed generously and come with plenty of hash browns. I got pancakes instead of toast. I was stuffed beyond belief and satisfied. I have gone back several times since and enjoy their consistency enough to write a thank you. And I always get a strawberry shake lol.

data.title: The best breakfast that I've had in Palatine
data.text: My husband and I  stop here at least once a Month and I always order the same thing.  I love   their Breakfast!

data.title: Good experience
data.text: Went here for breakfast kind of on a whim.  A couple of things stood out to me:  the genuinely friendly service and how hard EVERYONE is working to make your experience there a good one.  Small example:  I like my hash browns very well done - and I made sure my server knew this.  Before they were brought to me (I was seated at the counter), I heard her "reject" the hash browns as not being well done enough. I waited a little while - but you know what - they were served EXACTLY like I prefer them.  They were worth the wait.  I'll go back the next time I'm in the area.

data.title: Ok for breakfast, skip lunch
data.text:
This is advertised as a Greek diner but you will not find anything Greek on the menu for lunch.
Acceptable for breakfast but there are definitely better breakfast places in Palatine like The Red Apple or Grammy D's just across the street.
We had a really underwhelming lunch here recently and just cannot recommend it. Their hours state they are open until 3, but they are closing up at 2:30. The owner almost ran us down leaving at 2:30.
There is a very local regular crowd here for breakfast but they don't eat lunch here either.

data.title: Great service and very good food
data.text:
The food is always quite good and the service is impeccable.....too fast sometimes.
If you're looking for a freindly place with good food and great service this is it!!!!
We have only done breakfast here but we've done it many, many times.

data.title: For years and years, the best Breakfast/ Lunch spot in town!
data.text:
Try this pleasant  place for extensive breakfast items and nice lunches.
   Our meals are always prepared as ordered - try the steel cut oatmeal with all the fixings, or any of the excellent
 waffle combinations; my favorite has the bacon crumbled
 on top, as well as mixed in the batter. The children like the 
skillets, my daughter sticking to her Veggie Skillet.
  Super friendly servers and hosts keep the very  good Kona
coffee flowing.  (They have a decent decaf, as well).
 Even though we've relocated, Cafe Fourteen is a must-stop
each time we visit Illinois!

data.title: The soup alone was great
data.text: We used to go here for dinner before but they switched 6-3 seven days a week but since I was passing through at lunch time I thought I would give it a try again. The soup alone was amazing. It was cream of potatoe but it was more like baked potatoe soup with bacon , cheese and chives on top 'mmm' the cranberry turkey sandwiches were very good and some thing different. The other person with me on this trip had a turkey burger and it was slightly over done but had good flavor. The bread basket had sliced French bread with good taste but a little dry. I hope all restaurants will eventually wrap bread in the bread basket to keep it fresh and not handled a lot. I would say over all a good rating especially because of the soup.

data.title: A Noon Time coffee shop
data.text: Food is ok, service is friendly.  Prices can seem a bit high, but they give you a load of food when you order a sandwhich.  Open only until mid afternoon.

data.title: Large delicious entrees
data.text: We went to eat on a Sunday morning about 11:00AM, and I had a sandwich, which came with some and fries. It was very delicious cream of chicken soup. I think it was the best soup I ever had. My boyfriend ordered a breakfast dish, and loved it. The manager is so nice and was walking around talking to everyone and joking with customers. Our server was fantastic and very friendly. It is open for breakfast and lunch and we would definitely go back there. The bathrooms were very clean, and that says a lot about a restaurant.

data.title: decent moderately priced...
data.text: decent moderately priced family restaurant.
